  "prompt": "Where did the name Hollywood undead come from?",
  "response": "The band members have explained in interviews that the name \"Hollywood Undead\" came from their early days when they were creating music in a friend's home studio in Hollywood, California. They wanted a name that represented the party-rock style they were developing and the idea of being underground artists in the Hollywood music scene. The \"Undead\" part of the name suggests a rebellious, non-conformist attitude that goes against mainstream expectations.",
